  "poem": {
    "content": "The future whispers on bamboo leaves,\nA history etched in fragile green,\nWhere ancient trees begin to grieve,\nA frost that coats a forgotten scene.\n\nA panther’s shadow, a silent dash,\nAcross the path where dreams once lay,\nAn addict’s tremor, finding ash,\nAnd hope that turns to disarray.\n\nA hamster whirls, a frantic plea,\nTo put the pieces back in place,\nTo find within the thorny tree,\nA flicker of forgotten grace.\n\nTo shrug off winter's heavy hand,\nAnd close the door on yesterday,\nA very simple, heartfelt stand,\nTo simply breathe and truly play.\n\nA gift lies hidden in the snow,\nEnjoy its warmth, before it flees,\nA silent promise, soft and low,\nWhispered within the frozen trees.",
